# DotGitHub Project Structure

This is a TypeScript monorepo for managing GitHub Actions workflows and configurations. The project uses a CDK-style approach for generating GitHub Actions.

## Core Architecture

- **Monorepo Structure**: Uses Bun workspaces with packages in `packages/` and examples in `examples/`
- **Main Packages**: 
  - `@dotgithub/core` - Core functionality and constructs
  - `@dotgithub/cli` - Command-line interface
- **Entry Points**: 
  - CLI: [packages/cli/src/index.ts](mdc:packages/cli/src/index.ts)
  - Core: [packages/core/src/index.ts](mdc:packages/core/src/index.ts)

## Key Directories

- `packages/core/src/constructs/` - CDK-style constructs for building workflows
- `packages/core/src/plugins/` - Construct system for extending functionality
- `packages/core/src/types/` - TypeScript type definitions
- `packages/cli/src/commands/` - CLI command implementations
- `examples/` - Example projects showing usage patterns

## Configuration

- Main config: [package.json](mdc:package.json) (root)
- TypeScript: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) (root)
- Core package: [packages/core/package.json](mdc:packages/core/package.json)
- CLI package: [packages/cli/package.json](mdc:packages/cli/package.json)

## Build System

- Uses Bun as package manager and runtime
- TypeScript compilation with strict settings
- Vitest for testing
- Changesets for version management